{
  "success": true,
  "query": "engineering database schema SQL errors",
  "results": [
    {
      "layer": 3,
      "layer_name": "Cross-Company Patterns",
      "header": "Database & Migrations",
      "content": "### Database & Migrations\n- **Database migrations as deployment prerequisite**: Migrations execute before app startup; if migration includes schema updates for features, app must start successfully after migration completes; verify no app errors in logs post-deploy\n- **render.yaml explicit migration execution**: Include `npm run migrate` in build steps to guarantee migrations run before app starts; forces migration execution during build without relying on app startup hooks\n- **Ghost migrations and schema mismatches**: Migration system may record completion without actual schema changes; `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` silently skips if table exists with different schema from older code; detect via 500 \"relation does not exist\" errors on API calls; if migration expected columns that don't exist, table was skipped by IF NOT EXISTS logic; fix by dropping conflicting old tables before recreation in migration (zero data loss if empty), clearing migration records from `_migrations` table, and re-running migrations; subsequent INSERTs will now find correct schema\n- **Legacy column NOT NULL constraints block INSERT**: When schema migrates from old model to new model, old NOT NULL columns with no defaults remain from `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` skip; new INSERT logic omitting legacy columns fails immediately; fix: ALTER TABLE to DROP NOT NULL and SET defaults on all legacy columns\n- **Idempotent startup schema creation**: Use CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS in server.js before route handlers; runs every deploy; detects and recovers from ghost migrations; tables exist before first API call\n- **Idempotent data seeding on startup**: Use ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING in INSERT statements to repopulate tables without duplicates on redeploy; allows feature data (admin users, tech lead signals, company profiles, category mappings, fictional authors, demo stories, founding members) to be rebuilt from source code rather than relying on external API seeding; bypass unreliable third-party APIs by seeding realistic sample data directly; data persists indefinitely, updates propagate on next deploy\n- **Stale migration tracking prevents seed re-runs**: Migration runner tracks applied migrations by name; updating migration file contents alone won't re-trigger if name already exists in `_migrations` table; must delete stale migration record from database to force re-execution of updated seed data\n- **Migration file naming fallback pattern**: When migration files export missing `name` property, migration system can crash or record NULL names in `_migrations` table; add filename-based fallback in migrate.js to compute name from filename if export missing\n- **Parameterized query array handling**: When inserting array columns into PostgreSQL via parameterized queries, pass raw JavaScript arrays directly — never use `JSON.stringify()` on array parameters; the `pg` driver automatically converts JS arrays to PostgreSQL array format (e.g., `{val1,val2}`); stringifying produces JSON syntax that PostgreSQL rejects with \"malformed array literal\" errors",
      "relevance": "113%"
    },
    {
      "layer": 3,
      "layer_name": "Cross-Company Patterns",
      "header": "Deployment & Infrastructure",
      "content": "### Deployment & Infrastructure\n- Stack: Express + PostgreSQL/Neon, deployed on Render\n- Port 10000 standard for Express servers on Render\n- **Render health check endpoint**: Must serve `/health` (not `/api/health`); failed health checks cause silent rollback to previous deploy; place health route at TOP of server.js BEFORE all middleware to ensure instant 200 response without falling through to 404 handler; both `/health` and `/api/health` can coexist; enhanced health endpoint tests database connectivity and returns 503 when services degraded; support optional query param `?check=db` to return 503 if database connection fails\n- **Trust proxy for rate limiting AND session cookies**: Add `app.set('trust proxy', 1)` immediately after Express app creation, before any middleware; tells Express to trust X-Forwarded-For header from load balancer; rate limiting then sees actual client IPs instead of proxy IP; value `1` means \"trust exactly one proxy hop\" — correct for Render's single load balancer layer; CRITICAL for session cookie security: Render terminates SSL at load balancer, so Express sees HTTP without this setting, refuses to set `Secure` cookie flag, browser rejects insecure session cookie, user stays logged out despite successful auth → perpetual 401 redirect loops\n- **Session persistence before response**: Use explicit `req.session.save(callback)` in auth routes (signup, login) to guarantee session persists to PostgreSQL before HTTP response sends; prevents race condition where cookie set but database write still pending when browser receives response\n- **Render build script requirement**: package.json must include \"build\" script; Render runs `npm run build` on deploy and fails without it; script can be no-op (`\"build\": \"echo done\"`) for Node-only apps without frontend compilation\n- **Package.json dependency verification**: All `require()` statements in server.js, route files, and db connection modules must have corresponding entries in package.json dependencies; missing entries cause deploy failures even if code is syntactically correct; use `npm install [package] --save` before committing code that imports new modules; previous commits may have written code referencing modules without installing them — audit git history for orphaned imports\n- Zero-downtime deploys: use deferred FK constraints, avoid schema locks during migration\n- Chunked uploads (5MB) for Render's body-size limit\n- Blocked platforms: Reddit, Medium, Twitter (all 403)\n- **Service worker caching chain failures**: Three-layer cache system (browser + service worker + server headers) can break when: (1) express.static() serves HTML before custom no-cache routes execute (route ordering bug), (2) service worker uses cache-first strategy for HTML instead of network-first, (3) service worker file itself has no cache-busting headers; fix requires: route reordering to prioritize no-cache endpoints, network-first strategy for HTML assets, cache version bumps (e.g., `atomency-v3`), cache-busting params on service worker (`?v=timestamp`), and explicit `Pragma: no-cache, Expires: 0` headers; users see stale content despite successful deploys until hard refresh (Ctrl+Shift+R); two-minute window after fix where old service worker still active; subsequent deploys become visible immediately after service worker update installed\n- **Deploy verification pattern**: Wait 2-3 min post-deploy, curl endpoints to confirm old code gone, verify new features live before marking task complete\n- **Deploy status lag on Render**: `build_in_progress` status may persist >8 min despite successful build logs; wait 5+ min, then trigger manual re-deploy if stuck; verify file size/content changes via curl before assuming stale cache; app logs empty until build completes and app starts\n- **Stale static asset verification**: Check `Content-Length` and `Last-Modified` headers to confirm new assets served; size change confirms fresh deployment",
      "relevance": "26%"
    },
    {
      "layer": 3,
      "layer_name": "Cross-Company Patterns",
      "header": "Current Cross-Company Patterns (engineering) (9847 tokens)",
      "content": "## Current Cross-Company Patterns (engineering) (9847 tokens)",
      "relevance": "24%"
    },
    {
      "layer": 3,
      "layer_name": "Cross-Company Patterns",
      "header": "Static Content & SPA",
      "content": "### Static Content & SPA\n- **Static HTML extensionless routing**: Configure `express.static()` with `{ extensions: ['html'] }` option to auto-resolve `/pricing` → `public/pricing.html` without explicit routes; eliminates extensionless 404 errors for HTML files; if option absent, add explicit 301 redirects for clean URLs\n- **Static HTML pages in public folder**: Create `.html` files in `public/` directory for landing pages, media kits, policy pages, legal documents, PWA interfaces, analytics dashboards, user preference pages, admin login pages, invite join pages, FAQ pages; files accessible at `/filename.html` automatically via express.static(); no route handlers needed; enables rapid deployment of marketing/content pages without server code changes; include footer links for discoverability across all static pages\n- **SPA routing priority, server-rendered routes, and click interceptor exclusions**: React/Vue/Svelte SPAs in `client/dist/` take routing precedence over static files in `public/` when both paths exist; legacy HTML files in `public/` never served if SPA exists; edits to static HTML files have no effect — edit SPA source instead and rebuild bundle; server-rendered routes (e.g., `/cockpit`, `/glass`, `/glasshud`) must be excluded from SPA click interceptor to allow full-page navigation; if SPA click handler grabs all navigation, add exclusion list so browser performs full navigation to server route instead of client-side pushState + render(); PWA interfaces require full page navigation, not SPA client-side routing\n- **Dedicated shareable pages for live broadcast experiences**: Create parameterized routes (e.g., `/live/:slug`) that render full broadcast experience with theme selector, status indicators, viewer count, and animated components; include Open Graph meta tags (title, description, image, URL) for rich social media previews; dynamic OG images improve click-through on social shares\n- **Landing page SEO + conversion optimization**: Meta tags (title, description, keywords), Open Graph tags (Facebook/LinkedIn previews), Twitter Cards, JSON-LD schema (Google rich snippets), sitemap.xml, robots.txt, semantic HTML, ARIA roles; conversion elements: clear value prop, pain-point headline, competitor comparison, \"How It Works\" 3-step visual, FAQ addressing objections, trust signals (\"Free Forever\", \"No CC\", \"2-min setup\"), 7+ CTAs at strategic points (hero, comparison, features, pricing, footer); page flow: Hero → Comparison → How It Works → Features → Social Proof → Pricing → FAQ → Final CTA\n- **Modal forms on landing pages with async submissions**: Create `.html` modal UI with form inputs for capturing data on static pages without backend routes; use fetch API for async form submission to API endpoint; enables conversion capture on marketing pages without requiring full server routes\n- **Static file zip regeneration pattern**: Projects serving downloadable zips of source code require explicit regeneration when new features merge; zip files in `public/` don't auto-update from source file changes; regenerate entire zip with `zip -r filename.zip source/files`, commit, and push to trigger auto-deploy; stale zips persist across deploys until explicitly overwritten; file size change confirms regeneration captured new content; if multiple zip paths exist, regenerate ALL copies to maintain parity\n- **Static HTML asset desyncing from dynamic content**: When static HTML files contain hardcoded lists (avatars, equipment options, configs), they don't auto-update when corresponding dynamic pages or databases change; grep for all relevant containers across files to ensure feature parity; items missing from one page but present in another indicate incomplete sync; affects selector grids, dropdown options, configuration sections\n- **Branding synchronization across multiple files**: When rebranding exists in multiple files (page titles, hero badges, about sections, stats displays, philosophy statements, category pages), grep for old brand terms across entire codebase BEFORE search-and-replace; single missed instance creates inconsistent user experience; verify grep count matches expected occurrences; regenerate static HTML/zip files if they contain branding text; static files don't auto-update from renamed variables or content changes\n- **Auth flow navigation**: Link directly to auth page with URL parameters to control form mode; use `?mode=login` to display login form, `?mode=signup` for signup form; homepage can offer separate \"Log In\" and \"Join\" CTAs pointing to same auth page with different parameters; eliminates need for toggle discovery on auth page itself",
      "relevance": "24%"
    },
    {
      "layer": 1,
      "layer_name": "Domain Knowledge (This Company)",
      "header": "Database & Connection Pooling (Feb 10, 2026)",
      "content": "## Database & Connection Pooling (Feb 10, 2026)\n- **Pool config**: 25 connections, `connectionTimeoutMillis: 10s`, `idleTimeoutMillis: 30s`\n- **Key tables**: `job_applications`, `work_experience` (NOT NULL: `company_name`, `title`), `candidate_skills` (`level` INT 1-5), `portfolio_projects` (`title` NOT NULL), `offers` (30 cols, `title` NOT NULL), `practice_sessions`, `feedback`, `question_bank`, `mock_sessions`, `tts_cache`, `activity_log`, `country_configs` (8 seeded), `payroll_*` (5 tables), `scheduled_interviews`, `interview_analysis`, `jobs`, `pipeline_stages` (7 canonical: Applied, Screening, Phone Screen, Technical, Offer, Accepted, Rejected)\n- **Phase 3 tables**: `memory_events`, `memory_objects`, `memory_relationships`, `recruiter_preferences`, `candidate_match_breakdown` (7D: skills/exp/edu/salary/location/interviews/assessments), `match_feedback`\n- **Query optimization**: DISTINCT + ORDER BY fixed; slow queries >200ms tracked; pool exhaustion eliminated",
      "relevance": "19%"
    }
  ]
}

